						               													<description>In &amp;quot;Obscure Battles Volume 6 &amp;ndash; A Cruel Sea&amp;quot;, the player takes the role of a Submarine commmander trying to locate and destroy enemy shipping on a patrol.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a exclusively solitaire game: you don&amp;rsquo;t need any other player to play the game. Extremely fast playing and simple but detailed , fun game - just a A3 for your map board, the game is extremely easy to play. Just roll a single D6 and pick the targets then see if you can execute a successful attack and then survive to tell the tale !&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game comes with 8 Submarines: German Type 21 and 7C from WW2 and UC/III from WW1, French Surcouf, Japanese Junsen 2 , US Gato from WW2, Soviet Foxtrot and one special yellow submarine :) .&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play the standart game or you can also design your own missions using the supplied Submarine Info , Target ad Escort Type Cards. There are more Submarine types and loadouts that are provided as part of the optional packs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your targets are selected from  different decks of cards such as different freighter types, fishing vessel, troop Ships, tankers, capital warships etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your submarine will not be safe out there: there are several usual ASW escorts such as Destroyers, Frigates, ASW Planes, Corvettes and and even Q-Ships.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is also special set of &amp;quot;named&amp;quot; Target and Escort cards that come with their own name such &amp;quot;HMS Saltash Castle&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;USS England&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;IJN Shigure&amp;quot; and more.&amp;#10;Finally, the combat cards give you the expected unexpectedness of the life at sea.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
